          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>San Francisco</placeName>
                                        <date>Dec. 15. 1852</date>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Revd Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">Dear friend</p>
                              <p rend="indent(5)">I send you enclosed<lb/> Draft on <persName>Mess.
                                                  M. Cauffman &amp; Co</persName>,
                                                  <placeName>Phila.</placeName> Drawn by<lb/>
                                        <persName>Roggenburger &amp; Co</persName>, for $24.00,
                                        which I have collected for<lb/> the Occident, as per
                                        enclosed statement; &amp; enclose you also<lb/> a fresh
                                        subscription for the O.; had I more Time to<lb/> spare &amp;
                                        our Californians would devote more Time in<lb/> reading your
                                        intellectual work, I could, no Doubt have<lb/> sent you a
                                        larger list of Subscription.</p>
                              <p>I have recd your Letter, &amp; am sorry, that I cannot<lb/> comply
                                        with your wishes for informing you, how<lb/> Jewish affairs
                                        progress; however that much I can<lb/> tell you, that Jewish
                                        Families are getting quite Numerous<lb/> in <placeName>San
                                                  Francisco</placeName>, &amp; of late we had also
                                        several Mar-<lb/>-riages taking place. The Jewish Population
                                        all over<lb/>
                                        <placeName>California</placeName> is very numerous, but our
                                        Religion is<lb/> not by any means kept up in generality, as
                                        it should be.<lb/> We have two Synagogues here, one Polish
                                        &amp; one German,<lb/> which are open every
                                        “<add>שבת</add>”, but are not very well attended,<lb/> &amp;
                                        it is only on “<add>יום טוב</add>”, that you have the
                                        opportunity of<lb/> witnessing the Synagogues crowded, where
                                        there is generally<lb/> not Room enough to seat ½.</p>
                              <p>It saves me some Trouble, <del>when</del> if I collect the
                                        Subscriptions</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>immediately, &amp; you will notice several on my a/c who<lb/> have
                                        paid in advance. You will also be kind enough<lb/> to send
                                        me the a/c what <persName>Roggenburger &amp; Co</persName>
                                        in <placeName>California</placeName><lb/> owes you.</p>
                              <p>It was told me by several whose subscription<lb/> to the O. I have
                                        sent the Last Time, that they have not<lb/> recd the O. You
                                        will please therefore, to be exact in<lb/> making a plain
                                        Direction; as our Post office arrangement<lb/> is none of
                                        the Best.</p>
                              <p>Business in general has been very good with us for<lb/> the last
                                        10-12 Mos. &amp; Goods in almost all Branches<lb/> have paid
                                        well to import; some articles always<lb/> pay very well in
                                                  <placeName>California</placeName>; as for
                                        Instance<lb/> Flour is worth from $40 to $45—pr.
                                        Barrell,<lb/> which cost at Home no more than $4.50 pr
                                        Barrel.<lb/> I could give you more Information about
                                        Business<lb/> but I am aware, it is of no Interest to
                                        you—<lb/> as you are no Doubt aware, money making &amp;<lb/>
                                        speculating is all the go—&amp; one's attentions is
                                        almost<lb/> entirely directed to that.</p>
                              <p><persName>Mr. &amp; Mrs. Roggenburger</persName> desire their kind
                                        Regards<lb/> to you; they have arrived <sic>save</sic>;
                                        &amp; live very hand<lb/>-somely &amp; very convenient,
                                        &amp; Enjoy themselves; they live<lb/> “<add>כשר</add>”
                                        &amp; I am boarding with them, which gives me the
                                        op-<lb/>-portunity of reminding myself, that I am a
                                        “Secr”<lb/> Hoping, you will soon write to me a large letter
                                        &amp;c, &amp; that this<lb/> may find you in good Health</p>
                              <p rend="indent(9)">I Remain your true friend</p>
                              <p rend="indent(9)">
                                        <persName role="author">Cauffman H Meyer</persName>
                              </p>
                    </body>
